        <h2 class="pgm-ap-origin__h2">It Started With His Sister.</h2>
        <div class="pgm-ap-origin__body">
          <p>Growing up, Mike watched his sister deal with debilitating chronic pain. She saw doctors, tried physical therapy, and was told to manage it. Nothing fixed it. Frustrated and desperate for a real answer, Mike dove into the science of structural alignment — and discovered the Egoscue Method.</p>
          <p>The Egoscue Method starts with a simple premise: most chronic pain isn't an injury. It's a postural misalignment. When your skeleton is out of its designed position, muscles compensate, joints wear unevenly, and pain follows. Fix the structure, fix the pain.</p>
          <p>Mike enrolled at Egoscue University in Irvine, California — the same institution that trains practitioners who work with professional athletes, Olympians, and celebrities. He became a Certified Postural Alignment Specialist and put the method to work for his sister. It worked.</p>
          <p>That result changed everything. Mike knew he had to share it.</p>
