          Do I need any equipment?
          <svg class="pgm-ap-faq__chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M5 8l5 5 5-5"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <p class="pgm-ap-faq__a">No. Every exercise in the program is designed to be done at home using only your body and a floor. Some exercises use a wall, a chair, or a block — items you already have.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="pgm-ap-faq__item">
        <summary class="pgm-ap-faq__q">
          I've had surgery or have a serious condition. Is this safe for me?
          <svg class="pgm-ap-faq__chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M5 8l5 5 5-5"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <p class="pgm-ap-faq__a">The Egoscue Method is non-impact and non-manipulative. It has been used safely by people recovering from surgery and managing chronic conditions. However, you should always consult your physician before starting any new exercise program.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="pgm-ap-faq__item">
        <summary class="pgm-ap-faq__q">
          How is this different from yoga, stretching, or physical therapy?
          <svg class="pgm-ap-faq__chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M5 8l5 5 5-5"/></svg>
